-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----
PLACEHOLDER_REPLACE_POST_DEPLOY_WITH_REAL_ED25519_PUBKEY_FROM_AUTHORIZATION_SERVER
-----END PUBLIC KEY-----
# This is a placeholder bundled with the OSS package shape so importers
# don't fail on `open(oauth_pubkey.pem).read()`. The contents are NOT a
# valid Ed25519 public key — any attempt to use this file for actual JWT
# verification will fail at parse time. Founder must replace with the real
# pubkey PEM after the OAuth authorization server is deployed and the
# keypair is generated.
#
# To extract the real pubkey post-deploy:
#   aws secretsmanager get-secret-value \
#     --secret-id tessera/oauth/jwt-signing-key-prod \
#     --query SecretString --output text \
#     | python3 -c "
#       import sys
#       from cryptography.hazmat.primitives import serialization
#       priv = serialization.load_pem_private_key(sys.stdin.read().encode(), password=None)
#       print(priv.public_key().public_bytes(
#         serialization.Encoding.PEM,
#         serialization.PublicFormat.SubjectPublicKeyInfo).decode())
#     " > tessera/auth/oauth_pubkey.pem
#
# Or fetch from the live JWKS endpoint and convert:
#   curl https://tessera.cloudmorph.ai/oauth/jwks.json
# (The OSS package will fetch JWKS at runtime if this file is invalid, as
#  a fallback path — see cloudmorph-tessera/tessera/auth/oauth_rs.py for
#  the JWKS-cached verification.)
